713
00:52:30,240 --> 00:52:33,480
You're in charge.
You're the headmaster now.

714
00:52:33,480 --> 00:52:36,000
So from now on,
he's your pupil.

715
00:52:37,640 --> 00:52:40,920
So, from now on, boy...

716
00:52:40,920 --> 00:52:43,120
you do as I say.

717
00:52:43,120 --> 00:52:44,960
- Yes, sir.
- All right.

718
00:52:44,960 --> 00:52:48,920
Now to start off, I want you
to read these books.

719
00:52:48,920 --> 00:52:53,520
- All of them?
- That, my boy, is a mountain of knowledge.

720
00:52:53,520 --> 00:52:58,240
- But l, but I can't read.
- What, what? What? Then I don't suppose you know how to write?

721
00:52:58,240 --> 00:53:00,600
- No, sir.
- What do you know?

722
00:53:00,600 --> 00:53:03,240
- Well, l--
- Well, never mind. Never mind.

723
00:53:03,240 --> 00:53:06,840
We'll start at the bottom.
The ABC's.

724
00:53:06,840 --> 00:53:10,640
First the A,
and now the B.

725
00:53:10,640 --> 00:53:14,160
Loop and around
and there's the C.

726
00:53:14,160 --> 00:53:17,080
Merlin. Look.
I can write.

727
00:53:17,080 --> 00:53:19,800
Oh. Yes, yes.
That's very good, boy. Very--

728
00:53:19,800 --> 00:53:23,120
Henscratch, that's all.
Henscratch. Now, come on.

729
00:53:23,120 --> 00:53:27,360
D, E, F,
and now the G.

730
00:53:27,360 --> 00:53:30,840
You see, it's as simple as--
No, no, no! No, boy!

731
00:53:30,840 --> 00:53:35,000
Now, use your head. Use your head, will you?
How do you ever expect to learn anything?

732
00:53:35,000 --> 00:53:38,240
Archimedes!
Have you seen that, uh...

733
00:53:38,240 --> 00:53:41,440
flying machine model?

734
00:53:41,440 --> 00:53:45,720
I have nothing to do with your
futuristic fiddle-faddle, you know that.

735
00:53:45,720 --> 00:53:49,520
- What's that thing up there?
- Hmm? Oh, yes, of course.

736
00:53:49,520 --> 00:53:53,840
- Here we are.
- You mean man will fly in one of those someday?

737
00:53:53,840 --> 00:53:58,040
If man were meant to fly,
he'd have been born with wings.

738
00:53:58,040 --> 00:54:01,520
I am about to prove
otherwise, Archimedes...

739
00:54:01,520 --> 00:54:03,920
if you care to watch.

740
00:54:03,920 --> 00:54:06,880
Here she goes.

741
00:54:06,880 --> 00:54:09,960
No, no, no, no, no--

742
00:54:11,840 --> 00:54:15,880
Man'll fly all right.
Just like a rock.

743
00:54:18,880 --> 00:54:21,520
It would have worked if, if,
if, if it weren't for...

744
00:54:21,520 --> 00:54:24,160
this infernal beard!

745
00:54:33,960 --> 00:54:38,720
I never, never
in my whole--

746
00:54:43,840 --> 00:54:47,080
Man will fly someday,
I tell you.

747
00:54:47,080 --> 00:54:49,840
I have been there.
I have seen it.

748
00:54:49,840 --> 00:54:54,080
Oh, I do hope so.
I've always dreamed about flying--

749
00:54:54,080 --> 00:54:58,760
that I was a bird and that I could go sailing
all over the sky high above everything.

750
00:55:00,880 --> 00:55:02,800
Prestadigitonium.

751
00:55:02,800 --> 00:55:05,280
It's my favourite dream.

752
00:55:05,280 --> 00:55:09,520
Oh, but then I suppose
everybody dreams about flying.

753
00:55:09,520 --> 00:55:12,000
I'm a bird! I'm a bird!
I'm a bird!

754
00:55:12,000 --> 00:55:15,200
Hold it, boy.
Not so fast. Not so fast.

755
00:55:15,200 --> 00:55:19,200
First, l-- I'd better explain
the mechanics of a bird's wing.

756
00:55:19,200 --> 00:55:22,640
Now, these large feathers...

757
00:55:22,640 --> 00:55:25,360
are called the primaries.

758
00:55:25,360 --> 00:55:27,400
- And, uh--
- And, uh, since when...

759
00:55:27,400 --> 00:55:30,560
do you know all about
bird's wings?

760
00:55:30,560 --> 00:55:34,280
I have made an extensive study
of birds in flight. And l--

761
00:55:34,280 --> 00:55:38,240
And if you don't mind,
I happen to be a bird.

762
00:55:38,240 --> 00:55:42,280
All right, Mr Know-lt-All,
he's your pupil.

763
00:55:42,280 --> 00:55:44,720
- Ouch!
- Now, boy...

764
00:55:44,720 --> 00:55:48,360
flying is not merely
some crude mechanical process.

765
00:55:50,760 --> 00:55:54,280
It is a delicate art.
Purely aesthetic.

766
00:55:54,280 --> 00:55:56,200
Poetry of motion.

767
00:55:56,200 --> 00:55:58,600
And the best way to learn it
is to do it.

768
00:55:58,600 --> 00:56:02,360
Now, since we're pretty far up,
we'll start with a glide.

769
00:56:02,360 --> 00:56:06,720
Spread your wings way out,
way out. That's it. That's it.

770
00:56:06,720 --> 00:56:08,960
Now, fan your tail.

771
00:56:08,960 --> 00:56:12,720
Tippity-toe, tippity-toe,
and off we go.

772
00:56:15,880 --> 00:56:20,720
Now, tuck your feet under,
like me. That's it. That's the idea!

773
00:56:22,200 --> 00:56:25,440
- Whoa! What? Oh!
- And don't fight the air currents.

774
00:56:25,440 --> 00:56:27,560
Use them.

775
00:56:37,720 --> 00:56:40,120
Well, say, boy!

776
00:56:40,120 --> 00:56:42,440
That's pretty good.

777
00:56:42,440 --> 00:56:45,040
Well, boy,
you're a natural!

778
00:56:45,040 --> 00:56:48,720
Are you sure this is
the first time that you've--

779
00:56:48,720 --> 00:56:51,280
Wart! Wart!
Hawk! Hawk!

780
00:56:51,280 --> 00:56:53,560
Look out, boy!
Heads up! Wart!

781
00:56:56,120 --> 00:56:57,880
Archimedes! Help!

782
00:57:03,560 --> 00:57:06,240
Wart! Wart!

783
00:57:17,360 --> 00:57:19,080
Whoa! What? Oh!

784
00:57:26,520 --> 00:57:29,480
Sounds like someone's sick.
How lov--

785
00:57:29,480 --> 00:57:31,960
Oh, bat gizzards.
It's nothing but...

786
00:57:31,960 --> 00:57:35,280
a scrawny little sparrow
with a beak full of soot.

787
00:57:35,280 --> 00:57:38,560
Oh, I-I'm not really a sparrow.
I'm a boy.

788
00:57:38,560 --> 00:57:42,240
- A boy?
- Merlin changed me with his magic.

789
00:57:42,240 --> 00:57:44,360
He's the world's
most powerful wizard.

790
00:57:44,360 --> 00:57:46,400
Merlin. Ho-ho!

791
00:57:46,400 --> 00:57:49,920
Merlin, the world's
most powerful bungler.

792
00:57:49,920 --> 00:57:52,800
Why, boy, I've got more magic
in one little finger.

793
00:57:54,560 --> 00:57:58,280
Now, don't tell me you've never
heard of the marvellous Madam Mim?

794
00:57:58,280 --> 00:58:00,840
Well, no, I don't guess so.

795
00:58:00,840 --> 00:58:04,800
Madam Mim? Oh! Good heavens,
good heavens, good heavens!

796
00:58:04,800 --> 00:58:08,800
My boy, I'm the greatest.
I'm truly marvellous!

797
00:58:08,800 --> 00:58:12,960
With only a touch
I have the power

798
00:58:12,960 --> 00:58:17,040
Zim zab rim bim
To whither a flower

799
00:58:17,040 --> 00:58:20,440
I find delight
in the gruesome and grim

800
00:58:20,440 --> 00:58:22,960
- Oh, that's terrible.
- Thank you, my boy.

801
00:58:22,960 --> 00:58:25,920
But that's nothing,
nothing for me.

802
00:58:25,920 --> 00:58:28,840
No! 'Cause I'm the magnificent...

803
00:58:28,840 --> 00:58:31,400
marvellous, mad Madam Mim.

804
00:58:31,400 --> 00:58:34,960
You know what?
I can even change size.

805
00:58:34,960 --> 00:58:38,640
I can be huge!
Ooh! Fill the whole house.

806
00:58:40,520 --> 00:58:43,600
I can be teeny
Small as a mouse

807
00:58:43,600 --> 00:58:47,120
Black sorcery
is my dish of tea

808
00:58:49,280 --> 00:58:52,760
Uh, it comes easy to me.
'Cause I'm the magnificent...

809
00:58:52,760 --> 00:58:55,000
marvellous, mad Madam Mim.

810
00:58:58,280 --> 00:59:01,000
Marvellous, boy!
Marvellous, I'm marvellous!

811
00:59:03,600 --> 00:59:07,560
Say, lad, did you know that
I can make myself uglier yet?

812
00:59:07,560 --> 00:59:11,880
Well, that would be some trick.
Er, um, ah, I mean, uh--

813
00:59:11,880 --> 00:59:14,120
Want to bet? Boo!

814
00:59:15,400 --> 00:59:17,640
You see? I win, I win!

815
00:59:17,640 --> 00:59:21,720
Aren't I hideous, boy?
Perfectly revolting?

816
00:59:21,720 --> 00:59:24,880
- Well, uh, yes, ma'am.
- But you ain't seen nothin' yet.

817
00:59:24,880 --> 00:59:27,680
Watch this.

818
00:59:27,680 --> 00:59:31,800
I can be beautiful
lovely and fair

819
00:59:31,800 --> 00:59:36,000
Silvery voice
long purple hair

820
00:59:43,600 --> 00:59:48,080
But it's only skin deep
for zim zaberim zim

821
00:59:48,080 --> 00:59:52,720
I'm an ugly, old creep!
The magnificent, marvellous...

822
00:59:52,720 --> 00:59:55,680
mad, mad, mad,
mad Madam Mim.

823
00:59:58,560 --> 01:00:02,200
Now what do you think, boy?
Who's the greatest?

824
01:00:03,680 --> 01:00:08,200
Well, uh, Merlin's magic
is always, um, well, useful...

825
01:00:08,200 --> 01:00:10,480
uh, for something good.

826
01:00:10,480 --> 01:00:14,880
- And he must see something good in you.
- Oh, I suppose so.

827
01:00:14,880 --> 01:00:18,120
Yes, and in my book,
that's bad!

828
01:00:18,120 --> 01:00:22,400
So, my boy, I'm afraid
I'll have to destroy you.

829
01:00:22,400 --> 01:00:24,480
De-Destroy me?

830
01:00:24,480 --> 01:00:27,080
Yeah, I-I'll give you
a sporting chance.

831
01:00:27,080 --> 01:00:29,440
I'm mad about games,
you know.

832
01:00:29,440 --> 01:00:31,880
Yeah, well come on,
get going, boy.

833
01:00:31,880 --> 01:00:34,600
You gotta keep on your toes
in this game.

834
01:00:44,320 --> 01:00:46,240
I win, I win!

835
01:00:46,240 --> 01:00:48,640
Oh, the game's over.

836
01:00:51,000 --> 01:00:54,360
Why, you little devil, you! I'll
wring your scrawny little neck!

837
01:00:56,040 --> 01:00:59,920
Mim! Mim! Wha-Wha-What--
Eh, what was you up to?

838
01:00:59,920 --> 01:01:03,760
Uh! Me-Me-- Oh, Merlin!
Well, you're just in time.

839
01:01:03,760 --> 01:01:07,680
- We were playing a little game.
- She was gonna destroy me.

840
01:01:07,680 --> 01:01:10,840
And just what are you
gonna do about it?

841
01:01:10,840 --> 01:01:15,640
Want to fight?
Want to have a wizard's duel?

842
01:01:15,640 --> 01:01:20,160
- As you wish, madam.
- Well, come on, step outside.

843
01:01:20,160 --> 01:01:22,680
After you, madam.

844
01:01:37,000 --> 01:01:39,360
They're havin' a wizard's duel.
What's that mean?

845
01:01:39,360 --> 01:01:42,280
Oh, it's a battle of wits.
The players change themselves...

846
01:01:42,280 --> 01:01:46,320
to different things and, and attempt to,
uh, to destroy one another.

847
01:01:46,320 --> 01:01:48,080
De-Des-De-Destroy?

848
01:01:48,080 --> 01:01:50,160
But just watch, boy, just watch.
You'll get the idea.

849
01:01:53,480 --> 01:01:56,480
Now, first of all, if you
don't mind, I'll make the rules.

850
01:01:56,480 --> 01:01:58,400
Rules indeed!

851
01:01:58,400 --> 01:02:00,800
Why, she only wants rules
so she can break 'em!

852
01:02:00,800 --> 01:02:04,040
I'll take care of you later,
featherbrain.

853
01:02:04,040 --> 01:02:07,280
Now, rule one,
no mineral or vegetable.

854
01:02:07,280 --> 01:02:10,960
Only animal. Rule two,
no make-believe things...

855
01:02:10,960 --> 01:02:13,400
Like, uh, oh,
pink dragons and stuff.

856
01:02:13,400 --> 01:02:16,320
Now, rule three,
no disappearing.

857
01:02:18,160 --> 01:02:20,560
- Rule four, no cheating.
- All right, all right.

858
01:02:20,560 --> 01:02:23,600
Now, pace off ten.

859
01:02:23,600 --> 01:02:27,280
One, two, three, four--

860
01:02:27,280 --> 01:02:30,400
- Merlin! She disappeared!
- Huh? Ah-- Duh-- Bah-- Mim!

861
01:02:30,400 --> 01:02:32,760
Now, you made the rules!

862
01:02:38,640 --> 01:02:40,680
Ouch!

863
01:02:46,520 --> 01:02:48,520
- Change to somethin' else, Merlin.
- Ah-- Buh-- Y-Yes...

864
01:02:48,520 --> 01:02:52,240
yes, yes, yes,
give me time to think.

865
01:02:52,240 --> 01:02:56,080
- Ah, higgety-piggety. Ah, duh
-- No, no, no, no, no. - Quick, Merlin, hurry!

866
01:02:56,080 --> 01:02:58,200
Ah-- Duh-- Hoppity-hip-hip.

867
01:02:58,200 --> 01:02:58,920
Ha-ha!

868
01:03:00,680 --> 01:03:03,840
Got me tail, now!
Madam, just a minute.

869
01:03:03,840 --> 01:03:06,240
Ah-- D-D--
This is not the-the-the-the--

870
01:03:11,400 --> 01:03:13,960
- Come on! Something bigger!
- Something smaller!

871
01:03:13,960 --> 01:03:15,840
Mi-Mi-Mim, Mi-Mim,
Mi-Mim Mi-Mi--

872
01:03:15,840 --> 01:03:16,840
Ooh!

873
01:03:22,960 --> 01:03:27,160
Merlin! No disappearing.

874
01:03:27,160 --> 01:03:29,080
Whoo!

875
01:03:41,120 --> 01:03:42,960
Ouch!

876
01:03:49,640 --> 01:03:51,960
Mim? Mim?
Are-Are-Are you--

877
01:03:51,960 --> 01:03:53,840
Now-- Gah-- What-What--
W-W-What's going on here?

878
01:03:53,840 --> 01:03:56,880
You, you-- You big blimp!

879
01:04:07,560 --> 01:04:09,320
Squash me, will ya?

880
01:04:14,440 --> 01:04:17,120
Ah, ah, ah, ah, Merlin!

881
01:04:18,360 --> 01:04:20,800
- Ouch! Ooh!
- Bravo!

882
01:04:23,720 --> 01:04:26,640
Oh, just you wait!
Just you wait! You're gonna pay!

883
01:04:42,320 --> 01:04:45,760
So you want to play rough,
do ya?

884
01:04:47,720 --> 01:04:52,840
All right, Merlin. I'll
smash you good, you old crab!

885
01:04:53,920 --> 01:04:56,960
Jehoshaphat!

886
01:04:56,960 --> 01:05:01,000
Here I come, Mim,
ready or not.

887
01:05:02,880 --> 01:05:05,560
Merlin, you wouldn't dare!

888
01:05:16,440 --> 01:05:18,520
Now, now, Mim, Mim!
No-No dragons, remember?

889
01:05:18,520 --> 01:05:22,400
Did I say no purple dragons?
Did l?

890
01:05:36,440 --> 01:05:38,760
I win, I win!

891
01:05:38,760 --> 01:05:42,480
Oh, that horrible old witch!
I'll, I'll peck her eyes out!

892
01:05:42,480 --> 01:05:44,600
Huh, no, no.
No, no, no.

893
01:05:47,560 --> 01:05:49,880
- He's gone!
- Disappeared.

894
01:05:49,880 --> 01:05:54,280
Madam, I have not disappeared.
I am very tiny.

895
01:05:54,280 --> 01:05:57,320
I'm a germ. A rare disease.

896
01:05:57,320 --> 01:06:00,160
I'm called "malagolintomontorosis"...

897
01:06:00,160 --> 01:06:02,680
and you caught me, Mim!

898
01:06:02,680 --> 01:06:03,930
What?

899
01:06:05,160 --> 01:06:07,840
First, you break out
into spots.

900
01:06:10,000 --> 01:06:14,000
Followed by hot
and cold flashes.

901
01:06:15,640 --> 01:06:17,520
Then violent sneezing.

902
01:06:21,640 --> 01:06:23,680
Huh! Watch it, boy!

903
01:06:23,680 --> 01:06:28,080
Oh! Er-- You-You-You-You
sneaky old scoundrel!

904
01:06:35,160 --> 01:06:37,640
Oh, it's not too serious, madam.
Ah, you should recover...

905
01:06:37,640 --> 01:06:42,080
in a few weeks and be as good, uh--
Ah, heh-heh-- I-l mean as bad as ever.

906
01:06:42,080 --> 01:06:44,520
But, ah, I would suggest
plenty of rest...

907
01:06:44,520 --> 01:06:49,160
and lots and lots
of sunshine!

908
01:06:49,160 --> 01:06:51,560
I hate sunshine!

909
01:06:51,560 --> 01:06:55,240
I hate horrible,
wholesome sunshine!

910
01:06:55,240 --> 01:06:59,840
I hate it, I hate it!
I hate, hate, hate, hate--

911
01:06:59,840 --> 01:07:03,760
You were really great, Merlin,
but-but you could've been killed.

912
01:07:03,760 --> 01:07:06,800
It was worth it, lad, if you
learned something from it.

913
01:07:08,080 --> 01:07:10,320
Knowledge and wisdom
is the real power.

914
01:07:10,320 --> 01:07:13,800
Right you are, Wart,
so stick to your schooling, boy.

915
01:07:13,800 --> 01:07:17,640
Oh-Oh, don't worry, I will, sir.
I will, oh, I really will.

916
01:07:19,480 --> 01:07:23,520
We will sing all night
and all day we will fight

917
01:07:23,920 --> 01:07:27,760
For the blue oak tree
on the field of white

918
01:07:27,760 --> 01:07:32,880
For the blue oak tree
on the fie-ie-ie-ie-ield

919
01:07:32,880 --> 01:07:33,840
Of white

920
01:07:40,440 --> 01:07:44,560
Here's to victory in London
for my son, Kay!

921
01:07:44,560 --> 01:07:47,920
Sir Kay. I've been knighted,
don't forget.

922
01:07:47,920 --> 01:07:51,040
No-o, of course, son,
of course.

923
01:07:51,040 --> 01:07:54,240
Ah, here's to Sir Kay.
And who knows?

924
01:07:54,240 --> 01:07:56,400
The future king
of all England!

925
01:07:57,560 --> 01:08:00,920
- Watch it, will ya?
- Kay the king?

926
01:08:00,920 --> 01:08:03,440
What a dreadful thought.

927
01:08:03,440 --> 01:08:05,680
Sir Ector! Sir Ector!

928
01:08:05,680 --> 01:08:08,000
Hobbs has come down
with the mumps!

929
01:08:08,000 --> 01:08:11,440
Face all-all-all
puffed up like a toad!

930
01:08:11,440 --> 01:08:13,880
Then Kay'll need another squire,
hang it all.

931
01:08:13,880 --> 01:08:17,680
- Hmm. Wart, you're it.
- I'm what, sir?

932
01:08:17,680 --> 01:08:20,000
Kay's squire.
You're going to London, boy.

933
01:08:20,000 --> 01:08:22,920
Oh, Sir Ector!
Whoa! What? Whoa!

934
01:08:26,040 --> 01:08:28,960
Merlin! Archimedes! Merlin!

935
01:08:31,440 --> 01:08:34,360
Merlin, look!
I'm a squire!

936
01:08:34,360 --> 01:08:35,360
Hah!

937
01:08:37,200 --> 01:08:40,880
Oh. Uh, very nice, boy.

938
01:08:40,880 --> 01:08:46,600
Yes, indeed. A fine monkey suit
for polishing boots.

939
01:08:46,600 --> 01:08:49,000
It's-it's what
all the squires wear.

940
01:08:49,000 --> 01:08:51,920
And I thought you were
going to amount to something!

941
01:08:51,920 --> 01:08:55,720
I thought you had
a few brains!

942
01:08:55,720 --> 01:08:58,440
Great future. Hah!

943
01:08:58,440 --> 01:09:02,120
A stooge for that
big lunk, Kay.

944
01:09:02,120 --> 01:09:05,320
Congratulations, boy!

945
01:09:05,320 --> 01:09:08,480
What do y-- What do you want
me to be? I'm nobody.

946
01:09:08,480 --> 01:09:12,240
You-- You don't know a thing
about what's goin' on today.

947
01:09:12,240 --> 01:09:15,040
I-I-I-I'm lucky
to be Kay's squire.

948
01:09:15,040 --> 01:09:18,040
D-- Oh! D--
Of all the idiotic--

949
01:09:18,040 --> 01:09:21,720
Y-Y-Y-- I--
Blow me to Bermuda!

950
01:09:29,320 --> 01:09:31,280
Where-- Uh, where did he go?

951
01:09:31,280 --> 01:09:34,240
- To Bermuda, I suppose.
- Where's that?

952
01:09:34,240 --> 01:09:38,040
Oh, an island way off somewhere
that hasn't been discovered yet.

953
01:09:38,040 --> 01:09:40,000
Will he ever come back?

954
01:09:40,000 --> 01:09:42,920
Who knows?
Who knows anything?

955
01:09:47,520 --> 01:09:50,440
For the crown
of all England...

956
01:09:50,440 --> 01:09:53,040
let the tournament begin.

957
01:10:10,760 --> 01:10:14,000
Oh, Kay, now
it's up to the swords.

958
01:10:14,000 --> 01:10:18,960
Swords? Swords?
Ah-- Oh, no! Kay?

959
01:10:18,960 --> 01:10:20,400
What? What?

960
01:10:20,400 --> 01:10:23,760
I, eh--
I-l-l forgot your sword.

961
01:10:23,760 --> 01:10:26,320
Forgot my sword?

962
01:10:26,320 --> 01:10:29,040
I-- I-l left it
back at the inn.

963
01:10:29,040 --> 01:10:32,920
Why, you bungling little fool!
I'll-- Oof!

964
01:10:32,920 --> 01:10:36,480
You better get it!
Or don't you dare come back!

965
01:10:41,440 --> 01:10:43,680
Let me in! Let me in!

966
01:10:43,680 --> 01:10:46,560
Somebody please!
Please let me in!

967
01:10:46,560 --> 01:10:49,360
It's no use, boy.
They've all gone to the tournament.

968
01:10:49,360 --> 01:10:53,360
Oh, what'll I do?
Kay's got to have a sword.

969
01:10:53,360 --> 01:10:56,120
Look, boy! Look!
There in the churchyard.

970
01:10:56,120 --> 01:10:59,240
A sword!
Oh, Archimedes, a sword!

971
01:11:01,200 --> 01:11:03,160
You're gonna have a time
pullin' it out.

972
01:11:04,600 --> 01:11:06,760
Huh! Watch it, boy!

973
01:11:14,240 --> 01:11:16,080
Better leave it alone!

974
01:11:16,080 --> 01:11:19,240
But Kay's got to have
a sword.

975
01:11:21,440 --> 01:11:23,840
Now, come on, quick.
Let's get out of here!

976
01:11:26,760 --> 01:11:29,120
Y-You're up next, son.
Uh, better get ready.

977
01:11:29,120 --> 01:11:31,320
Kay, Kay, here's a sword.

978
01:11:32,840 --> 01:11:34,960
This is not my sword!

979
01:11:34,960 --> 01:11:37,840
Hold on, Kay!
Wait a minute.

980
01:11:37,840 --> 01:11:41,720
"Whoso pulleth out
this sword--"

981
01:11:41,720 --> 01:11:44,560
Ooh, eh-- It's the sword
in the stone!

982
01:11:44,560 --> 01:11:49,200
- The sword in the stone? It can't be.
- But look. It is!

983
01:11:49,200 --> 01:11:52,600
- It's the marvellous sword.
- Hold everything.

984
01:11:52,600 --> 01:11:56,760
Someone's pulled the sword
from the stone.

985
01:11:56,760 --> 01:11:58,760
Where did you get it, Wart?

986
01:11:58,760 --> 01:12:02,000
I, l-l pulled it out of an anvil
that was on a stone...

987
01:12:02,000 --> 01:12:04,720
i-in, in a churchyard.

988
01:12:06,160 --> 01:12:09,040
- That's funny!
- The lad's a young Samson!

989
01:12:10,640 --> 01:12:13,960
You're making a fool of us, boy.
Now tell the truth.

990
01:12:13,960 --> 01:12:17,200
- But I did, sir. Ow! Ooh!
- Then come on, prove it.

991
01:12:17,200 --> 01:12:19,600
- Ouch!
- Back to the stone with you.

992
01:12:19,600 --> 01:12:23,600
- Yes, prove it.
- Come on, prove it.

993
01:12:30,800 --> 01:12:33,480
All right, boy,
let's have the miracle.

994
01:12:38,160 --> 01:12:39,960
Now, wait a minute!

995
01:12:39,960 --> 01:12:43,280
Anyone can pull it
once it's been pulled.

996
01:12:45,360 --> 01:12:48,800
Go to it, Kay.
Give it all you got.

997
01:12:48,800 --> 01:12:51,760
Put your back into it!

998
01:12:51,760 --> 01:12:52,960
- Here now!
- Here, here, here!

999
01:12:52,960 --> 01:12:55,120
- Push him and see.
- It's my turn. One side!

1000
01:12:55,120 --> 01:12:57,040
- Pull this thing.
- Hold on, that's not fair.

1001
01:12:57,040 --> 01:12:59,440
I say we let
the boy try it.

1002
01:12:59,440 --> 01:13:02,840
That's what I say.
Give the boy a chance.

1003
01:13:02,840 --> 01:13:04,760
Go ahead, son.

1004
01:13:17,080 --> 01:13:20,600
It's a miracle
ordained by heaven.

1005
01:13:20,600 --> 01:13:22,680
This boy is our king.

1006
01:13:22,680 --> 01:13:25,800
Well, by Jove.

1007
01:13:25,800 --> 01:13:28,560
- What's the lad's name?
- Eh, Wart.

1008
01:13:28,560 --> 01:13:30,840
Oh, uh, I mean Arthur.

1009
01:13:30,840 --> 01:13:36,240
- Hail King Arthur!
- Hail King Arthur! Long live the king!

1010
01:13:36,240 --> 01:13:39,560
- Long live King Arthur! Long live the king.
- I can't believe it!

1011
01:13:39,560 --> 01:13:42,000
- Ooh, forgive me, son.
- Hail King Arthur.

1012
01:13:42,000 --> 01:13:44,320
- Long live the king. Long live...
- Forgive me.

1013
01:13:44,320 --> 01:13:46,680
- King Arthur. Long live the king.
- Oh, please don't, sir.

1014
01:13:46,680 --> 01:13:49,120
- Kay, bow down to your king.
- Hail King Arthur.

1015
01:13:49,120 --> 01:13:51,040
Long live the king.

1016
01:13:54,800 --> 01:13:57,600
- Hail King Arthur.
- So at last, the miracle...

1017
01:13:57,600 --> 01:14:01,880
had come to pass in that
far off time upon New Year's Day...

1018
01:14:01,880 --> 01:14:05,680
and the glorious rein
of King Arthur was begun.

1019
01:14:09,520 --> 01:14:13,880
I can't be a king, Archimedes. I don't
know anything about ruling a country.

1020
01:14:13,880 --> 01:14:16,720
I told you to leave the thing
in the stone, boy.

1021
01:14:17,920 --> 01:14:20,600
I'll, I'll run away,
that's what I'll do.

1022
01:14:23,440 --> 01:14:24,920
They'll just have to get
somebody else.

1023
01:14:24,920 --> 01:14:28,160
Better take the side door, Wart.
Out the side door.

1024
01:14:32,480 --> 01:14:35,760
Hail King Arthur!
Long live the King!

1025
01:14:37,840 --> 01:14:40,400
There's another door. Over there,
over there! Come on, come on!

1026
01:14:44,600 --> 01:14:47,760
Long live King Arthur!
Long li--

1027
01:14:49,680 --> 01:14:51,640
Looks-Looks like
we're surrounded, boy.

1028
01:14:51,640 --> 01:14:55,200
Oh, Archimedes,
I wish Merlin was here.

1029
01:14:57,960 --> 01:15:00,320
Merlin! Merlin!

1030
01:15:05,080 --> 01:15:07,040
Oh, Merlin, you're back
from Ber-Ber-Ber--

1031
01:15:07,040 --> 01:15:10,320
Bermuda?
Yes, back from Bermuda...

1032
01:15:10,320 --> 01:15:13,360
and the 20th century.

1033
01:15:13,360 --> 01:15:16,400
And believe me,
you can have it.

1034
01:15:16,400 --> 01:15:21,520
One big modern mess!
Alakazam!

1035
01:15:21,520 --> 01:15:23,440
I'm in an awful pickle.
I'm king.

1036
01:15:23,440 --> 01:15:26,000
Ooh, he pulled the sword
from the stone.

1037
01:15:26,000 --> 01:15:29,520
Ha-ha!
Of course, of course!

1038
01:15:29,520 --> 01:15:33,360
King Arthur and his
Knights of the Round Table.

1039
01:15:33,360 --> 01:15:36,960
- Round table?
- Oh, uh, w-would you rather have a square one?

1040
01:15:36,960 --> 01:15:39,200
Oh, no. Round'll be fine.

1041
01:15:40,960 --> 01:15:42,960
Boy, boy, boy.

1042
01:15:42,960 --> 01:15:44,960
You'll become
a great legend.

1043
01:15:44,960 --> 01:15:49,080
They'll be writing books
about you for centuries to come.

1044
01:15:49,080 --> 01:15:51,920
Why, they might even make
a motion picture about you.

1045
01:15:53,320 --> 01:15:56,440
- Motion picture?
- Oh.

1046
01:15:56,440 --> 01:16:00,720
Uh, well, um-- Uh, that's
something like television...

1047
01:16:00,720 --> 01:16:02,640
without commercials.

1048
01:16:05,520 --> 01:16:10,000
Hail King Arthur
Long live the King

1049
01:16:16,000 --> 01:16:20,000
Text editing: Emanuel

